{"type": "article", "id": 42347, "title": "总有人提醒你坐久了起来站站，这个干脆发明了自动的｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-06-25T22:53:19Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 18678, "name": "Fuseproject"}, {"id": 27564, "name": "Peleg Design"}, {"id": 41766, "name": "Cossmann_Jacobitz"}, {"id": 954, "name": "Herman Miller"}, {"id": 41767, "name": "VDA BANGKOK"}, {"id": 41768, "name": "Maskull Iasserre"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 8, "praise_count": 123, "image": "img/article/article_show/20170625105847NaHIAfmOGRC6W9ed.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Live OS by Herman Miller &amp; Fuseproject</h3><p>为了帮助办公族改变久坐的不良习惯，美国家具公司 <a href=\"http://www.hermanmiller.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Herman Miller</a> 和著名工业设计师 Yves Behar 领导的设计工作室 <a href=\"https://fuseproject.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Fuseproject</a> 联手打造了一个名为 Live OS 的智能化办公家具系统。这个系统的核心设备是一个能够追踪员工行为的感应器，用户可以在 App 中预设改变姿势的时间。当感应器和可调节的办公桌配套使用时，感应器就会以震动或是点亮的方式提醒人们休息一下，按下后办公桌就会及时调整高度。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201706251059291NPOw3Tt7z6nkJMd.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749577\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625105930VgrW6vFt3nysxoiB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749577\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2017062510593051StHoN0ZhCGdfr3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562606\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625105931d2uZxwEpNL1yBlOI.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Wetsleeve</h3><p>进行户外运动时，你有没有觉得水瓶携带起来还是不够方便？这个名为 Wetsleeve 的袖套型水壶是纽约一家同名初创公司历时三年打造的解决方法。袖套内置了一个容量为 350 毫升的袋子，并且配备了可拆卸的硅胶制饮水口。装水后只需要将顶部的粘扣带扣上，塞入袖套即可。袖套本身由防水、隔热材料制成，减少体温对液体的影响。除此之外，内侧还设计了两个暗袋，可以放入零钱或是钥匙等小物。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/thewetsleeve/wetsleeve-wearable-hands-free-hydration/\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹链接</a>，售价从 39 美元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625105942vnD8bO9IdKLh3TrH.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.588235\" data-format=\"png\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625105943Eg3YQ2pJqIyBOH0x.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.588235\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625105946YGE9cOTDVLjt3ISg.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563235\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Bloom by Peleg Design</h3><p>即使不擅长把餐巾折成花，你也可以用它来装饰餐桌。最近，来自以色列霍隆理工学院（Holon Institute of Technology）的 Yam Amir 为 <a href=\"https://www.peleg-design.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Peleg Design</a> 设计了一个名为 Bloom 的餐巾夹，看起来就像是柔软的花茎。只要将餐巾轻轻一卷放入空隙内，就能变身为一朵绽放的花，简洁又很讨巧。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.peleg-design.com/shop/bloom.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">预售链接</a>，售价为 16 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110003rzEcAmQ8SUxFDsuZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.623313\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110003LFtfUTWgX6uInmkD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.623313\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110003qZyjT1uRg2S6OtPJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.623313\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Covo by Cossmann_Jacobitz</h3><p>来自德国的双人设计组合 <a href=\"http://www.cossmann-jacobitz.com/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cossmann_Jacobitz</a> 最近为宠物用品公司 <a href=\"https://www.miacara.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">MiaCara</a> 设计了一款名为 Covo 的狗窝，可替换的垫子被一圈弯木所包围，在为汪星人提供舒适的同时也不会破坏室内的装饰风格。为了便于移动，底部还特意留出两个缺口。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110015MhG2rwkzHUKfCoQu.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666250\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110015eOAlvmd57SuEpJhy.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.560000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>TASTE&amp;Co by VDA BANGKOK</h3><p><a href=\"http://vda.co.th/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">VDA BANGKOK</a> 是一家来自泰国的创意公司，为了帮助国内的小生产者们推广生意，他们创办了一个名为 TASTE&amp;CO 的品牌。这些卡通风格的包装是团队为旗下的果干产品线设计的，顾客可以很轻松地从拟人化形象中找到它们与真实水果的联系，比如有着棕色外壳的椰子就变成了皮肤黝黑粗糙、一头灰发的老爷爷。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110031BIEOXjKxqvzDiWct.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.662151\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110030yA3glVQfW75I9kDY.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.524979\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110030g5bOrCJHpakscdlB.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.524979\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110030iTW6DdHawSnjY9sF.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.524979\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110031jIXbdCcYsUu38hfD.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.524979\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Schrodinger’s Wood by Maskull Iasserre</h3><p>用“千钧一发”来形容加拿大艺术家 <a href=\"http://maskulllasserre.com/home.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Maskull Iasserre</a> 这件名为“薛定谔的木头”的最新雕塑作品再合适不过了。为了呈现出这种紧张感，擅长将生活中常见物品以雕塑形式重现的 Iasserre 选择在一整根树干上直接进行雕刻，小心地将中间部分挖空成似乎很快就要断裂的绳索。</p><p><br></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110046RD5J3XnCIuESQYqj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.504000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201706251100467CsoSXADav9eUyIT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.769000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170625110046FDWuX2khbZU1q4ng.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.504000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}